place.name: WEDDINGTON
place.gazetteerText: WEDDINGTON, a parish in Nuneaton district, Warwick; 1 mile N of Nuneaton r. station. Post town, Nuneaton. Acres, 911. Real property, £2,155. Pop., 74. Houses, 10. W. Castle is the seat of E. Lees, Esq. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Worcester. Value, £278.* Patron, Mrs. Hall. The church was built in 1733. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
